heaviest_rainfall.status: Record amounts of rain fell over 29.3 hours today with a total accumulation of 22.76mm.  It fell at 8.3 mm per hour at times and ranked 7th from our records.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 7th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 29.3 hours.  22.76mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
